<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-166-074 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 625 344</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Sources  May 1991 v2 n5 p50(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Reduce business mailing costs. (PSI Associates' Envelope Managermail printing utility)(Forum)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Claiborne, Dave.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   PSI Associates (Products).andO;Product:   Envelope Manager (Utility program) (Design and construction).andO;Topic:     Mail PreparationUtility ProgramsLabelsBar Codes.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>REDUCE BUSINESS MAILING COSTS Despite the recent postal rate increases, youcan still save money when you mail, thanks to a $145 database package calledEnvelope Manager (PSI Associates, Palo Alto, CA, 415-321-2640).andM;To speed and automate the mail, the United States Postal Service is markingletters with its special POSTNET bar code.andP;  This code allows automatedsorting of letters in carrier route order.andP;  Currently, most POSTNET codes aresprayed on with special machines during mail sorting.andP;  If more senders barcoded their letters, however, the Postal Service estimates it could save $40million to $50 million a year for each 1 percent of the letters premarked.andM;Consequently, the recent postal rate increases include incentives toencourage sender-printed POSTNET coding.andP;  If you mail 250 letters at one timewith the bar codes already in place, you can save 5.7 cents per first-classletter.andP;  In June, a 2-cent discount is planned for individual letters.andM;The two difficulties in obtaining this discount, however, are printing thePOSTNET code on the envelopes and obtaining the correct ZIP+4 code.andP;  ZIP+4 isan address code you need that corresponds to POSTNET.andP;  The Envelope Managersolves both problems.andM;Envelope Manager prints all sizes and types of envelopes, labels, and flyerswith the POSTNET code.andP;  Addresses are maintained in its internal database,sortable for selected mailings.andP;  The product works best with laser printerssuch as the Hewlett-Packard LaserJet Series II and III, and the IBM 4019, butproduces acceptable results on many HP-compatible printers.andM;To make it easy to obtain the necessary ZIP+4 code, PSI has developedDial-a-ZIP and incorporated it into Envelope Manager.andP;  Once you enter anaddress in the database, pressing a single key initiates modem contact withPSI's CD-ROM full of ZIP+4 address codes.andP;  In less than 10 seconds, youraddress is uploaded, the database queried, and the ZIP+4 code returned to theEnvelope Manager database.andO;</TEXT></DOC>